Here's a short JavaScript code snippet that demonstrates a simple function to greet a user:

```javascript
function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

console.log(greet("World"));
```

This function takes a `name` parameter and returns a greeting string. The `console.log` statement demonstrates how to use the function.@EOF@[JavaScript, code snippet, function, greeting, console.log]
